      "interpretation": "IG is baseline-sensitive (Sundararajan ┬¦3; Kapishnikov 2021; Sturmfels 2020) ŌĆö and the VCS content path lets us say PRECISELY in what. The raw attribution MAGNITUDE moves a lot: IG_i = (x_iŌłÆx0_i)┬ĘŌłéy/Ōłéx_i, so max|IG| ranges 0.0ŌĆ”0.0 across the four baselines (the (xŌłÆx0) factor), and the completeness reference y(x0) changes too. BUT the faithfulness CORR/RANKING is INVARIANT here (╬öcorr=0.0): the forward-exact one-hot read makes Ōłéy/Ōłéx = e_idx a CONSTANT (independent of x and the path), so every baseline puts ALL of IG's nonzero mass on the SAME content byte ŌćÆ the per-cause ranking, hence corr/precision@k/del-ins, does not move. The ONE way the baseline changes the RANKING is the DEGENERACY: when a baseline byte EQUALS the content byte's value, (xŌłÆx0)=0 there and IG VANISHES at the only cell it could rank (the `zeros` baseline on a 0-valued content byte) ŌĆö `n_baselines_ig_alive` flags it; on-distribution baselines avoid it. Net: on this differentiable substrate IG's faithfulness is robust to the baseline EXCEPT at the degeneracy ŌĆö a sharper, measured version of the textbook 'IG is baseline-sensitive' caveat.",
